Placeholder so `bundle.resources` glob `resources/mw-server*` matches during a
plain `cargo build` (tauri-build validates resource globs at build time, before
any binary is bundled). The REAL self-contained engine — the release `mw-server`
binary — is dropped next to this file by `scripts/bundle-server.{sh,ps1}` right
before `tauri build` (SPEC §4.1 / plan §3 e3). At runtime the shell resolves the
exact platform binary (`mw-server` / `mw-server.exe`), so this text file is
ignored. Do not remove: without a matching file, `cargo build -p mailwoman-desktop`
fails in CI/clippy jobs that don't run bundle-server.
